page.title: 14ECOLOGY
page.content:
BIRDS: By the canal, the whitethroat, willow warbler and bullfinch are found The whinchat, tree pipit, meadow pipit and curlew are found in the Mosses area. Specifically in the Wem Moss area are found the blackcap, willow tit, coal tit, linnet, yellow hammer, reed bunting, skylark, lapwing, stock dove and great spotted woodpecker.
INSECTS: These are some of the moth and butterfly species found: Butterflies Green hairstreak, orange tip, peacock, dingy skipper, small tortoiseshell Moths Emperor, treble bar, common heath
